#   Binary     : broscoli  (built from cmd/broscoli/main.go)
#   Last push  : 2026-05-04
#
# WHAT IT IS
#   broscoli is "🥦 a simple OSC command executor" — Holoplot's Go daemon
#   that listens for Open Sound Control (OSC) messages on a configured
#   UDP address:port, matches the message's address path against an
#   `actions:` map loaded from a YAML config, and runs each matched
#   action's shell command (parsed via `kballard/go-shellquote`).  The
#   typical deployment is "press a button on an OSC controller (TouchOSC,
#   QLab, Bitwig, etc.), run a sysadmin / lighting / playback command on
#   a remote host" — turning OSC into a lightweight RPC trigger.  All
#   structured log output flows through `rs/zerolog` with a TTY-aware
#   ConsoleWriter for human-readable terminal sessions.
#
# CLI ARGUMENT GRAMMAR  (verbatim from cmd/broscoli/main.go Go stdlib
#                       `flag.String` declaration)
#   broscoli [-config <FILE>]
#
#   Options (Go stdlib `flag` package — both `-name` and `--name` forms):
#     -config <FILE>     Config file to parse (YAML)  [default: config.yaml]
#     -h, -help          Show help (Go flag stdlib auto)
#
#   YAML config schema (Config struct in main.go):
#     port:    <uint16>          UDP port to listen on
#     address: <string>          UDP address to bind to
#     actions:                   map[string]*Action
#       <name>:
#         command: <string>      Shell command line to execute on match
#         wait:    <bool>        Whether to wait for command exit before
#                                accepting the next message
#
#   OSC dispatch:
#     - Incoming OSC messages whose address starts with `/action/`
#       trigger the action named by the suffix:  message at
#       `/action/foo` looks up `actions[foo]` in the config and runs
#       its `command:`.
#
# AXIS / CORPUS POSITION
#   Direct dependency on `github.com/hypebeast/go-osc` declared in go.mod
#   (pinned at v0.0.0-20220308234300-cec5a8a1e5f5) — the canonical Go
#   OSC library by Sebastian Ruml (hypebeast), implementing OSC 1.0 /
#   1.1 message + bundle encoding, address pattern matching, UDP server
#   + client surface.  broscoli's main loop uses `osc.NewServer(addr,
#   dispatcher)` and a custom `dispatchMessage(msg *osc.Message)` to
#   route incoming messages to the action map.  Verified via:
#     gh api repos/holoplot/broscoli/contents/go.mod
#       → github.com/hypebeast/go-osc v0.0.0-20220308234300-cec5a8a1e5f5
#     gh api repos/holoplot/broscoli/contents/cmd/broscoli/main.go
#       → import "github.com/hypebeast/go-osc/osc"
#   This entry is the Go=119 leader bump that continues Axis 64
#   (OSC / Open Sound Control Library) opened at R845 with
#   Rust=rosc (lpil/sonic-pi-tool).
#
#   No completion for `broscoli` ships with Apple zsh
#   (/usr/share/zsh/*/functions) or Homebrew zsh-completions
#   (/opt/homebrew/share/zsh/site-functions) — confirmed absent.
# ============================================================================

_broscoli() {
    _arguments \
        '-config[YAML config file to parse (default config.yaml)]:config file:_files -g "*.(yaml|yml)"' \
        '(- *)-h[show help]' \
        '(- *)-help[show help]'
}

_broscoli "$@"
